obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4497)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4497&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Finance Commission (Miscellaneous Provisions)`
  line `Act, 1951.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4498)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4498&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "the Commission" means the Finance Commission constituted by the`
  line `President pursuant to clause (1) of article 280 of the Constitution`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4499)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Qualifications for appointment as, and the manner of selection of, members of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4499&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman of the Commission shall be selected from among persons who have had`
  line `experience in public affairs, and the four other members shall be selected from among persons who--`
  line
  line `(a) are, or have been, or are qualified to be appointed as Judges of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) have special knowledge of the finances and accounts of Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) have had wide experience in financial matters and in administration; or`
  line
  line `(d) have special knowledge of economies.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4500)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Personal interest to disqualify members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4500&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Before appointing a person to be a member of the`
  line `Commission, the President shall satisfy himself that that person will have no such financial or other`
  line `interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a member of the Commission; and the President`
  line `shall also satisfy himself from time to time with respect to every member of the Commission that he has`
  line `no such interest and any person who is, or whom the President proposes to appoint to be, a member of the`
  line `Commission shall, whenever required by the President so to do, furnish to him such information as the`
  line `President considers necessary for the performance by him of his duties under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4501)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualifications for being a member of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4501&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for`
  line `being appointed as, or for being, a member of the Commission,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is of unsound mind;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) if he has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(d) if he has such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a`
  line `member of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4502)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of members and eligibility for reappointment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4502&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every member of the`
  line `Commission shall hold office for such period as may be specified in the order of the President appointing`
  line `him, but shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that he may, by letter addressed to the President, resign his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4503)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Conditions of service and salaries and allowances of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4503&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The members of the`
  line `Commission shall render wholetime or part-time service to the Commission as the President may in each`
  line `case specify, and there shall be paid to the members of the Commission such fees or salaries and such`
  line `allowances as the Central Government may, by rules made ^1[by notification in the official Gazette] in this`
  line `behalf, determine.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 7 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4504)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Procedure and powers of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 13 of 1955, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203&sectionId=4504&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00033_195133_1517807323203
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall determine their`
  line `procedure and in the performance of their functions shall have all the powers of a civil court under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record from any court or office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have power to require any person to furnish information on such points or`
  line `matters as in the opinion of the Commission may be useful for, or relevant to, any matter under the`
  line `consideration of the Commission ^1[and any person so required shall, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in sub-section (2) of section 54 of the Indian Income Tax Act, 1922 or in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, be deemed to be legally bound to furnish such information within the meaning of section 176 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 480 and 482 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of enforcing the attendance of witnesses, the local limits of the`
  line `Commission's jurisdiction shall be the limits of the territory of India.`
